This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with object detection using convolutional neural networks. The paper also involves designing a method for proposing object locations, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of deep convolutional layers suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves evaluating the performance of the proposed method, which may fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
